      <title>Lockheed Martin's Sikorsky unveils next generation Raider X helicopter</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANSikorsky, a company owned by Lockheed Martin, debuted Raider X, a light attack and reconnaissance helicopter concept on October 14 at the Association of the U.S. Army conference in Washington.The helicopter features two counter-rotating coaxial rotors and a push propeller, according to a news release from Lockheed Martin. The prototype has been submitted to partake in the Army's Future Attack Reconnaissance Aircraft Competitive Prototype program, Breaking Defense reports. Raider X will reach speeds of up to 250 knots and fly as high as 9,000 feet. It will also be able to perform high-speed maneuvers to a 60 degrees angle of bank. Lockheed Martin says the helicopter's rotors will allow it to carry out enhanced low-speed hover, off-axis hover as well as level acceleration and braking.Raider X will be part of Sikorsky's X2 line of aircraft.The company says that the helicopter will use designs and manufacturing used in other planes by Sikorsky and Lockheed Martin such as the CH-53K, CH-148 and F-35.Lockheed Martin says this will keep costs down and allow for more affordable upgrades.The helicopter is able to carry weapons, though the company did not specify which weapons will be taken onboard.Lockeed Martin says Raider X will utilize modern open systems architecture that facilitates reconfiguring or replacing sensors, other avionics and mission modules. RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Features of the helicopter and the helicopter taking off2. How fast and how high the helicopter can fly3. Helicopter performing a 60 degrees angle of bank4. The helicopter performs a low-speed hover, off-axis hover, level acceleration and braking5.The helicopter will use digital designs and manufacturing used in other aircraftVOICEOVER (in English): "Sikorsky, a company owned by Lockheed Martin, debuted Raider X, a light attack and reconnaissance helicopter concept on October 14 at the Association of the U.S. Army conference in Washington.""According to a news release from Lockheed Martin, the helicopter features two counter-rotating coaxial rotors and a push propeller.""Raider X will reach speeds of up to 250 knots and fly as high as 9,000 feet." "It will also be able to perform high-speed maneuvers to a 60 degrees angle of bank.""Lockheed Martin says the helicopter's rotors will allow it to carry out enhanced low-speed hover, off-axis hover as well as level acceleration and braking.""Raider X will be part of Sikorsky's X2 line of aircraft.""The company says that the helicopter will use designs and manufacturing used in other planes by Sikorsky and Lockheed Martin such as the CH-53K, CH-148 and F-35.""Lockheed Martin says this will keep costs down and allow for more affordable upgrades."SOURCES: Lockheed Martin, New Atlas, Breaking Defense https://news.lockheedmartin.com/2019-10-14-Sikorsky-Introduces-RAIDER-X-TM-a-NextGen-Light-Attack-Reconnaissance-Helicopter-Based-on-its-Proven-X2-Technologyhttps://newatlas.com/military/sikorsky-unveils-raider-x-light-attack-helicopter/https://breakingdefense.com/2019/10/raider-x-sikorsky-supersizes-s-97-for-army-scout/***]]></description>
